  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7106.27 sitting just below the GEX flip at 7112 in a PIN regime, dealers are currently net long gamma and likely buying this dip to hedge their short delta exposure. The massive negative gamma wall at 7115 (-8215.3M) creates a critical inflection point - any move back above 7112-7115 should trigger dealer selling as they flip to short gamma, while the positive gamma cushion at 7100 (+4292.5M) provides downside support. Watch for mean reversion back toward 7115-7120 given the stabilizing regime, but a break below 7100 could accelerate moves lower as dealers reduce hedge buying.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect a bounce back toward 7115-7120 unless we break below 7100 support.",
